      "comment": "BEAR'S HEAD (1) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (22.61) at this track over 400m. Leading chance again. LOCKDOWN (3) boasts a strong record this journey with five wins and four minors from 12 tries. Was out of placings last time (25.46) at Grafton in a NG, finishing sixth and beaten 3.5 lengths. Among the main chances. TORNADO ETHICS (4) is a well performed dog and winner of 10 races who is worth forgiving after finishing out of the placings at this track (22.62). Has a good record here at this journey. Has a strong record from box 4, including two wins. Cannot be taken lightly. KIARNI BAD GIRL (2) placed last start and is in the mix again.",
